 which can facilitate faster diagnosis and more effective treatment regimens.The hospital subsegment is also witnessing a trend toward the integration of EEG amplifiers with other advanced medical technologies, such as MRI and CT scans, for comprehensive diagnostic solutions. This integration allows for a more holistic approach to patient care, ensuring that all aspects of a patient's brain activity and overall health are monitored. Additionally, hospitals are increasingly focused on patient comfort and convenience, leading to the development of non-invasive EEG devices that offer greater ease of use and minimal discomfort. The rising demand for EEG amplifiers in hospitals is expected to continue growing as neurological disorders become more prevalent and technology continues to improve.</p><h3>Clinic Subsegment</h3><p>Clinics are another important application area for EEG amplifiers, particularly in the field of outpatient care. Clinics primarily use EEG amplifiers for the diagnostic assessment of patients suffering from neurological conditions like epilepsy, anxiety disorders, and attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD). EEG testing in clinics provides an efficient way for medical practitioners to monitor brain activity, make informed diagnoses, and plan treatment strategies. As the healthcare industry moves towards outpatient models of care, the demand for portable and easy-to-use EEG amplifiers has risen. Clinics are looking for devices that are not only cost-effective but also offer reliable results and minimal maintenance requirements.With an increasing focus on preventive healthcare, clinics are increasingly using EEG amplifiers for routine screenings, especially in patients who exhibit symptoms of neurological abnormalities. The rising awareness about brain health and the need for early diagnosis of disorders further boosts the demand for EEG amplifiers in clinics. Technological advancements are also pushing the development of wireless and mobile EEG